The former lawmaker who represented Kaura Namoda/ Birinin Magaji Federal Constituency of Zamfara State, Hon. Aminu Sank Jaji, has advised the leadership of the state chapter of the All Progressives Congress (APC) to always make wider consultations with stakeholders in the party. According to a press statement signed by the Publicity Secretary, Hon. Yusuf Idris Gusau, the former lawmaker advised the leadership to try and reach out to aggrieved members of the party. “APC is one family and we are not divided so the leadership has it as a Responsibility to unite everyone and make peat among each other,” he said. “Treat both old and new members with equal right and reunites aggrieved members.” The statement further noted that the advice was given when the leadership paid a solidarity visit to the former lawmaker’s residence in Abuja. It added that the state chairman of the party, Alhaji Tukur Umar Danfulani, commended the lawmaker and assured him that the leadership would do everything within its power to bring everyone under one umbrella.